CodeAlpha Bioinformatics Internship

Overview

This repository contains the work completed during my CodeAlpha Bioinformatics Internship. The internship provided hands-on experience in biological sequence analysis, data retrieval, and the use of bioinformatics tools for analyzing DNA and protein sequences.

Internship Details

- Internship: CodeAlpha Bioinformatics Internship
- Domain: Bioinformatics
- Role: Bioinformatics Intern

Tasks Completed

- Performed DNA and protein sequence analysis.
- Retrieved biological sequences from public databases such as NCBI and UniProt.
- Conducted sequence similarity analysis using BLAST.
- Studied sequence alignment and interpreted biological results.
- Documented observations and findings in a detailed internship report.

Tools & Resources Used

- NCBI
- UniProt
- BLAST
- FASTA Format
- Microsoft Word
- Microsoft Excel

Repository Contents

- Internship_Report.pdf – Detailed report of the internship tasks and results.
- images/ – Screenshots of analysis and results.
- sequences/ – Sample DNA and protein sequence files (FASTA format).
- results/ – Output files generated during the analysis.

Skills Gained

- Bioinformatics data analysis
- DNA and protein sequence analysis
- Biological database searching
- BLAST analysis
- Scientific documentation
- Data interpretation

